<mjml>
  <mj-head>
    <mj-style> h2, img, p { margin: 0; } td { padding-top: 0 !important; } p { margin-bottom: 10px; } </mj-style>
    <mj-font name="Roboto" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Roboto" />
    <mj-font name="Roboto+Serif" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Roboto+Serif:ital,opsz,wght@0,8..144,100..900;1,8..144,100..900&display=swap" />
  </mj-head>
  <mj-body background-color="#f0f1f3">
    <mj-spacer height="15px"></mj-spacer>
    <!-- Logo Header -->
    <mj-section background-color="#ffffff">
      <mj-spacer height="10px" />
      <mj-column padding="10px 12px 10px 12px" width="100%">
        <mj-spacer height="16px" />
        <mj-image padding="10px 12px" css-class="light_img" width="150px" src="https://www.presidentialsummary.com/logo.png" href="https://www.presidentialsummary.com" alt="" />
        <mj-divider border-width="1px" border-style="solid" border-color="lightgrey" padding="10px 0px" />
        <mj-text padding="10px 2px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="
              font-size: 16px;
              line-height: 1.4;
              margin-top:2px;
            ">Did you know the President of the United States receives a top-secret briefing on national security every morning?</p>
          <p style="
              font-size: 16px;
              line-height: 1.4;
            "><strong>In today’s edition:</strong> </p>
          <p style="
              font-size: 16px;
              line-height: 1.4;
              padding-left: 10px;
            ">→ Israeli hostages released</p>
          <p style="
              font-size: 16px;
              line-height: 1.4;
              padding-left: 10px;
            ">→ Model on conformity and anti-conformity</p>
          <p style="
              font-size: 16px;
              line-height: 1.4;
              padding-left: 10px;
            ">→ Is LA safe to visit?</p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-divider border-width="1px" border-style="solid" border-color="lightgrey" padding="0px 0px" />
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
    <!-- breaking news1  -->
    <!-- /breaking news 1 -->
    <mj-spacer height="10px" />
    <!-- Spotlight -->
    <mj-section css-class="mj_fsection" background-color="#ffffff" css-class="mj_fsection">
      <mj-column background-color="#ffffff" width="100%">
        <mj-text padding="2px 12px 0px 12px" font-family="Roboto" color="white">
          <h2 style="
          padding-top:14px;
          padding-bottom:8px;
          color:#4D3060;
            text-align: left;
            letter-spacing:6px;
            border-bottom:2px solid #4D3060;
            text-transform:uppercase;
              font-size: 20px;
              line-height: 1.2;
              font-weight: 300;
               
            ">SPOTLIGHT</h2>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
    <mj-section background-color="#ffffff">
      <mj-column>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto" color="#000000">
          <h2 style="
              font-size: 20px;
              line-height: 1.2;
              font-weight: 500;
              margin-top: 2px !important; 
            ">Political transfer of power</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.presidentialsummary.com/email/images/ps-jan-20-1.png" alt="Political transfer of power" href="https://www.presidentialsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4">Today, Donald Trump will be inaugurated as the 47th president. This inauguration is unique for many reasons. He is the second president, after Grover Cleveland, in US history to return to the presidency after losing a second term. The day also coincides with <a href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-20-01-2024-h1-1-martin-luther-king-day" target="_blank">Martin Luther King Day</a>, which has happened twice before. Some find it ironic that he claimed his rally on January 6th, 2021, had more attendees than Martin Luther’s famous “ I Have a Dream” speech on the March on Washington in 1963.</p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4;filter:blur(5px);">This is also the first inauguration day in 40 years to be moved indoors to the Capitol Rotunda <a href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-20-01-2025-h1-2-due-to-cold-weather" target="_blank">due to cold weather</a>. The temperature is expected to be around 23 degrees Fahrenheit, and the wind chills in single digits. The dignitaries and guests attending this event include former presidents and foreign leaders; however, they will skip the inaugural luncheon. Elon Musk, Mark Zuckerberg, and Jeff Bezos are expected to sit together with the cabinet nominees on the platform.</p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column> 
    </mj-section>
    <mj-spacer height="15px"></mj-spacer>
  </mj-body>
</mjml>